    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Cloud Custodian - Tools - Lambda Garbage Collector - Mugc]]></title>
    <link href="http://bprathap104.github.io/blog/2020/11/13/cloud-custodian-tools-lambda-garbage-collector-mugc/"/>
    <updated>2020-11-13T12:32:51+05:30</updated>
    <id>http://bprathap104.github.io/blog/2020/11/13/cloud-custodian-tools-lambda-garbage-collector-mugc</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Cloud Custodian provides a tool called MU Garbage collector(mugc.py), using which we can clear the unused Lamba policies that were earlier deployed using custodian tool.</p>

<p>For this we need the policy file which has the definition for the deployment of those Lambda policies</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>python tools/ops/mugc.py -c policies.yaml --present</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Lambda - 11th Greek Letter
Mu - 12th Greek Letter</p>

<p>Mu Garbage Collector is a Lambda Cleanup</p>
]]></content>
  </entry>
  
  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Cloud Custodian - Tools - Exporting Lambda Based Policies for Deploying Manually]]></title>
    <link href="http://bprathap104.github.io/blog/2020/11/12/cloud-custodian-exporting-lambda-based-policies-for-deploying-manually/"/>
    <updated>2020-11-12T22:26:19+05:30</updated>
    <id>http://bprathap104.github.io/blog/2020/11/12/cloud-custodian-exporting-lambda-based-policies-for-deploying-manually</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Custodian supports exporting the lambda policies by generating a zip and allows any non-custodian tool to deploy it in AWS Cloud</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>$ mkdir sam-deploy
</span><span class='line'>$ python policylambda.py -o sam-deploy -c policies.yml
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>$ cd sam-deploy
</span><span class='line'>$ aws cloudformation --template-file deploy.yml --s3-bucket mybucket &gt; cfn.yml
</span><span class='line'>$ aws cloudformation deploy cfn.yml</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
  </entry>
  
